- ping (icmp==internet control message protocol):
initial connectivity test (to eliminate kind of firewall or some other obstacles)

- netcat == read from and write to newtwork connections using tcp or udp:
check format of the request or checking if traffic reacing a destination
port scanning and file transfer, etd.

- tcpdump == utility to capture network traffic
no GUI

- wireshark == tool to analyze what was captured by tcpdump or other
has a GUI
analyze packets in real time or analyze uploaded file